## Logging Configuration

The project uses a redaction-aware logging pipeline (`src/main/utils/redact.ts`)
driven by the `logging` section of `resources/global-config.yaml`.

```typescript
// Main process - log through the configured pipeline, never via bare console.log
// in production code paths.
import { getLogger } from "@main/utils/logger"; // (add this helper if it doesn't exist yet)

const log = getLogger("my-module");
log.info("started");
log.error("failed", { err });
```

The standardized format (verbose mode, session IDs, location info) is
configured in `resources/global-config.yaml` under `logging`. Never configure
logging directly in your files. Always use the centralized configuration to
maintain consistent output across the entire application.

If a log is not showing up, check `resources/global-config.yaml` to see if the
corresponding level is enabled:

```yaml
logging:
    levels:
        debug: false
        info: true
        warning: true
        error: true
        critical: true
```

Redaction patterns live under `logging.redaction.patterns` and are applied to
every log line before it hits stdout. Add patterns there whenever you
introduce a new secret format (API keys, tokens, etc.).
